second period of stardom, during which Connery successfully developed the character of the father-mentor. Ten years after his retirement from acting, he was still rated as the most popular British star among American audiences.Exploring how Connery’s performances combine to form an all-encompassing screen legend, the book also considers how the actor embodied national identity, both on screen and through his public role as an activist campaigning for Scottish independence.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aMotion picture actors and actresseszGreat BritainvBiography. 4aFilm and Media Studies 2022. 7aBIOGRAPHY & AUTOBIOGRAPHY / Entertainment & Performing Arts.2bisacsh  aActing and Performance.  aAgeing.  aIconic star.  aJames Bond.  aMasculinity.  aMedia industry studies.  aNational identity.  aScottishness.  aSean Connery.  aStardom.1 aSpicer, Andrew, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 2022 eBook-Packagez978311128144540uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978152611910040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781526119100423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781526119100/original  a978-3-11-128144-5  Manchester University Press 2022 eBook-Packageb2022  aGBV-deGruyter-alles